<p>A Houthi-run court in Sanaa sentenced 17 people to death over alleged espionage for Israel, the United States and Saudi Arabia, according to rebel and media reports [aljazeera#1][timesofisrael#1][firstpost#1][newarab#1]. Rebel media said the executions were ordered by firing squad [newarab#1], and Houthi authorities are seeking public executions [aljazeera#1]. Two others received 10-year prison terms and one person was acquitted; a defense lawyer said the sentences can be appealed [newarab#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/wSRhPHaEUfmB1VxdPSVIdjrKCjwJfCGYSDV5VFuQw5nvsbMgYjckd2g4bKN9YHCVrDYLRYCwDyqkPktB-9Ji3UoFKJFIcRfwSkCPsyiwSkzcDd7tkMhpIkt8pO6SgxKJkq-m4PDTGlksi2HWj9hqpAJFfsn3EPt9mharih4ce46SWJzw-CE7Q2KoM6PPagbprRkdmwkdOWjVoJoGOag' alt='File image from coverage of Houthi-controlled Yemen amid ongoing conflict and legal actions.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>A Houthi court in Sanaa issued 17 death sentences for alleged espionage linked to Israel, the US and Saudi Arabia [aljazeera#1][timesofisrael#1][firstpost#1][newarab#1]</li><li>The Saba agency reported the executions were set to be carried out by firing squad [newarab#1]</li><li>Houthi authorities are seeking to conduct the executions publicly [aljazeera#1]</li><li>A man and a woman were each sentenced to 10 years in prison, and one defendant was acquitted; the verdicts can be appealed, according to defense lawyer Abdulbasit Ghazi [newarab#1]</li><li>Charges cited “espionage cells” linked to US, Israeli and Saudi intelligence, including recruiting others that enabled strikes causing deaths and major damage [timesofisrael#1][newarab#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Houthi authorities: They allege the convicted were part of “espionage cells” affiliated with American, Israeli and Saudi intelligence, and ordered executions by firing squad; authorities are seeking public executions [newarab#1][aljazeera#1] (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/houthis-sentence-17-death-over-spying-israel-us-saudi'>The New Arab; Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Defense counsel (Abdulbasit Ghazi): Ghazi said the defendants can appeal the sentences [newarab#1] (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/houthis-sentence-17-death-over-spying-israel-us-saudi'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>The Times of Israel: The outlet reports charges included recruitment enabling strikes causing deaths and major damage, possibly referencing Israeli bombings [timesofisrael#1] (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/yemens-houthis-sentence-17-to-death-over-alleged-spying-for-israel-us-saudis/'>The Times of Israel</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/23/houthi-court-sentences-17-to-death-accused-of-spying-for-israel-west'>Houthi court sentences 17 to death accused of spying for Israel, West</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/yemens-houthis-sentence-17-to-death-over-alleged-spying-for-israel-us-saudis/'>Yemen’s Houthis sentence 17 to death over alleged spying for Israel, US, Saudis</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/houthi-court-sentences-death-to-17-over-foreign-spying-13953305.html'>Houthi court sentences death to 17 over foreign spying</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/houthis-sentence-17-death-over-spying-israel-us-saudi'>Houthis sentence 17 to death over spying for Israel, US, Saudi</a> - newarab.com</li></ul>